{{Politics of Algeria}}
'''Parliamentary elections''' were held in [[Algeria]] on 20 September 1964.<ref>Nohlen, D, Krennerich, M & Thibaut, B (1999) ''Elections in Africa: A data handbook'', p47 {{ISBN|0-19-829645-2}}</ref> The country was a [[one-party state]] at the time, with the [[National Liberation Front (Algeria)|National Liberation Front]] as the sole legal party. As a result, the election took the format of a yes or no vote on the FLN.<ref name=N>Nohlen, D, Krennerich, M & Thibaut, B (1999) ''Elections in Africa: A data handbook'', p56 {{ISBN|0-19-829645-2}}</ref> Voter turnout was 85%.<ref name=N/>
==Results== {| class=wikitable style=text-align:right !Party !Votes !% |- |align=left|[[National Liberation Front (Algeria)|National Liberation Front]]||4,493,416||87.0 |- |align=left|Invalid/blank votes||12,785||– |- |align=left|'''Total'''||'''5,177,631'''||'''100''' |- |align=left|Registered voters/turnout||6,091,991||85.0 |- |colspan=3 align=left|Source: Nohlen et al. |}
