'''Expo 2020''' ({{lang-ar|<big>إكسبو</big> ٢٠٢٠}}) is a [[World Expo]] to be hosted by [[Dubai]] in the [[United Arab Emirates]], opening on October 20, 2020. The [[Bureau International des Expositions]] (BIE) general assembly in [[Paris]] awarded Dubai as the host on November 27, 2013.

==Parameters==
{{unreferenced section|date=January 2017}}
As a World Expo, it may be a maximum of six months in length and adhere to a wide universal theme that applies to all humanity. Past themes of Universal Expositions include "Man and His World" [[Montreal]] [[Expo 67]], "Leisure in the Age of Technology" [[Brisbane]] [[Expo 88]] and "Discovery" [[Seville]] [[Seville Expo '92|Expo 92]].

==Organization==
The main site of Expo Dubai 2020 will be a 438-hectare area (1083 acres) located between Dubai and Abu Dhabi cities, near [[Dubai emirate]]'s western border with [[Abu Dhabi emirate]].
The master plan, designed by the American firm [[HOK (firm)|HOK]], is organized around a central plaza, entitled ''Al Wasl'', enclosed by three large pavilions which will be built by Al-Futtaim Carillion, each one dedicated to a sub-theme.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.inexhibit.com/seed/expo-dubai-2020-a-preview |title=EXPO Dubai 2020 – a preview |publisher=Inexhibit magazine |accessdate=2016-02-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160217022200/https://www.inexhibit.com/seed/expo-dubai-2020-a-preview |archivedate=February 17, 2016 }}</ref>
Dubai has also been emphasizing on investments in various sectors such as economic growth, real estate, environmental avenues and public affairs. In recent times, Dubai has made major investments in Real Estate<ref>{{cite web|last=Nagraj|first=Aarti|title=Dubai Properties launches two-tower project|url=http://gulfbusiness.com/dubai-properties-launches-two-tower-project-business-bay/|accessdate=30 May 2016|publisher=Gulf Business}}</ref> as well as introduced a world’s largest Solar Power Project which is all set to start by Expo 2020.<ref>{{cite web|last=Nagraj|first=Aarti|title=Dubai launches world’s largest concentrated solar power project|url=http://gulfbusiness.com/dewa-launches-worlds-largest-concentrated-solar-power-project/|accessdate=2 June 2016|publisher=Gulf Business}}</ref> Apart from pumping money, the nation is also keen on giving equal prominence to public relationships. The initiative – Dubai Happiness Agenda, has 16 programmes under four themes that sums up 82 projects to be set in the city with an aim to make the city the happiest by 2020.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hamdan|first=Lubna|title=Dubai scores 89% on happiness index for government services|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/dubai-scores-89-on-happiness-index-for-government-services-633287.html|accessdate=29 May 2016|publisher=Arabian Business}}</ref> The Dubai Expo 2020 also would see a rise in the GDP as predicted by the International Monetary Fund.<ref>{{cite web|last=Al Heialy|first=Yasmin|title=Expo 2020 spending to help Dubai's economy outperform peers|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/expo-2020-spending-help-dubai-s-economy-outperform-peers-631173.html|accessdate=10 May 2016|publisher=Arabian Business}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=UAE Gears Up Ahead of Dubai EXPO 2020|url=https://www.shuraa.com/blog/2016/06/uae-gears-up-ahead-of-dubai-expo-2020.html|accessdate=16 June 2016|publisher=Shuraa Business Setup}}</ref>

There are reports which have analysed the recent economic downturn and predict that World Expo 2020 Dubai will lead to a property bubble, which might have far reaching consequences.<ref>{{cite web|last=Batrawy|first=Aya|title=Dubai world Expo bid stirs worry of second bubble|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/huff-wires/20131125/ml--dubai-world-s-fair-fears/?ir=homepage|publisher=Huffington Post}}</ref>  Furthermore, the expo has been very quiet recently and like many other projects in Dubai, some expo projects are cancelled. In other words the hype has died. <ref> https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=DV7bvalswuM  </ref>

