==Events== * [[379]] &ndash; Emperor [[Gratian]] elevates [[Theodosius I|Flavius Theodosius]] at [[Sirmium]] to ''[[Augustus (honorific)|Augustus]]'', and gives him authority over all the eastern provinces of the [[Roman Empire]]. * [[639]] &ndash; [[Clovis II]], king of [[Neustria]] and [[Kingdom of Burgundy|Burgundy]], is crowned. * [[649]] &ndash; [[Conquest of Kucha]]: The forces of Kucha surrender after a forty-day [[siege]] led by [[Tang dynasty]] general Ashina She'er, establishing Tang control over the northern [[Tarim Basin]] in [[Xinjiang]]. *[[1419]] &ndash; [[Hundred Years' War]]: [[Rouen]] surrenders to [[Henry V of England]], completing his reconquest of [[Normandy]]. *[[1511]] &ndash; [[Mirandola]] surrenders to the French. *[[1520]] &ndash; [[Sten Sture the Younger]], the [[Regent of Sweden]], is mortally wounded at the [[Battle of Bogesund]]. *[[1607]] &ndash; [[San Agustin Church (Manila)|San Agustin Church in Manila]] is officially completed; it is the oldest church still standing in the [[Philippines]]. *[[1661]] &ndash; [[Thomas Venner]] is [[hanged, drawn and quartered]] in London. *[[1764]] &ndash; [[John Wilkes]] is expelled from the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|British House of Commons]] for [[seditious libel]]. *[[1764]] &ndash; The world's first [[mail bomb]] severely injures the Danish Colonel Poulsen, residing at [[Børglum Abbey]]. *[[1788]] &ndash; The second group of ships of the [[First Fleet]] arrive at [[Botany Bay]]. *[[1795]] &ndash; The [[Batavian Republic]] is proclaimed in the Netherlands, bringing to an end the [[Republic of the Seven United Netherlands]]. *[[1806]] &ndash; Britain occupies the [[Dutch Cape Colony]] after the [[Battle of Blaauwberg]]. *[[1812]] &ndash; [[Peninsular War]]: After a ten-day siege, [[Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington]], orders British soldiers of the Light and third divisions to storm [[Ciudad Rodrigo]]. *[[1817]] &ndash; An army of 5,423 soldiers, led by General [[José de San Martín]], [[Crossing of the Andes|crosses the Andes]] from [[Argentina]] to liberate [[Chile]] and then [[Peru]]. *[[1829]] &ndash; [[Johann Wolfgang von Goethe]]'s ''[[Faust: The First Part of the Tragedy]]'' receives its premiere performance. *[[1839]] &ndash; The [[British East India Company]] captures [[Aden]]. *[[1853]] &ndash; [[Giuseppe Verdi]]'s opera ''[[Il trovatore]]'' receives its premiere performance in Rome. *[[1861]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] joins [[South Carolina]], [[Florida]], [[Mississippi]], and [[Alabama]] in declaring [[secession]] from the United States. *[[1862]] &ndash; American Civil War: [[Battle of Mill Springs]]: The [[Confederate States of America|Confederacy]] suffers its first significant defeat in the conflict. *[[1871]] &ndash; [[Franco-Prussian War]]: In the [[Siege of Paris (1870–71)|Siege of Paris]], [[Kingdom of Prussia|Prussia]] wins the [[Battle of St. Quentin (1871)|Battle of St. Quentin]]. Meanwhile, the French attempt to break the siege in the [[Battle of Buzenval (1871)|Battle of Buzenval]] will end unsuccessfully the following day. *[[1883]] &ndash; The first electric lighting system employing overhead wires, built by [[Thomas Edison]], begins service at [[Roselle, New Jersey]]. *[[1899]] &ndash; [[Anglo-Egyptian Sudan]] is formed. *[[1915]] &ndash; [[Georges Claude]] patents the [[neon discharge tube]] for use in advertising. * 1915 &ndash; [[German strategic bombing during World War I]]: German zeppelins bomb the towns of [[Great Yarmouth]] and [[King's Lynn]] in the United Kingdom killing at least 20 people, in the first major aerial bombardment of a civilian target. *[[1917]] &ndash; [[Silvertown explosion]]: A blast at a munitions factory in London kills 73 and injures over 400. The resulting fire causes over £2,000,000 worth of damage. *[[1920]] &ndash; The [[United States Senate]] votes against joining the [[League of Nations]]. * 1920 &ndash; The [[American Civil Liberties Union]] (ACLU) is founded. *[[1937]] &ndash; [[Howard Hughes]] sets a new [[Cross-America flight air speed record|air record]] by flying from Los Angeles to New York City in 7 hours, 28 minutes, 25 seconds. *[[1940]] &ndash; ''[[You Nazty Spy!]]'', the very first Hollywood film of any kind to satirize [[Adolf Hitler]] and the Nazis premieres, starring [[The Three Stooges]], with [[Moe Howard]] as the character "Moe Hailstone" satirizing Hitler. *[[1941]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: The Greek ''Triton'' (Y-5) sinks the Italian submarine ''Neghelli'' in [[Otranto]]. *[[1942]] &ndash; World War II: The [[Japanese conquest of Burma]] begins. *[[1945]] &ndash; World War II: [[Red Army|Soviet]] forces liberate the [[Łódź Ghetto]]. Of more than 200,000 inhabitants in 1940, less than 900 had survived the [[Nazism|Nazi]] occupation. *[[1946]] &ndash; General [[Douglas MacArthur]] establishes the [[International Military Tribunal for the Far East]] in Tokyo to try Japanese [[war crime|war criminals]]. *[[1953]] &ndash; Almost 72% of all television sets in the United States are tuned into ''[[I Love Lucy]]'' to watch [[Lucy Ricardo|Lucy]] [[Lucy Goes to the Hospital|give birth]]. *[[1960]] &ndash; Japan and the United States sign the [[Treaty of Mutual Cooperation and Security between the United States and Japan|US–Japan Mutual Security Treaty]] *[[1969]] &ndash; Student [[Jan Palach]] dies after setting himself on fire three days earlier in [[Prague]]'s [[Wenceslas Square]] to protest about the invasion of [[Czechoslovakia]] by the [[Soviet Union]] in 1968. His funeral turns into another major protest. *[[1974]] &ndash; China gains control over all the [[Paracel Islands]] after [[Battle of the Paracel Islands|a military engagement]] between the naval forces of China and [[South Vietnam]] *[[1977]] &ndash; President [[Gerald Ford]] pardons [[Iva Toguri D'Aquino]] (a.k.a. "[[Tokyo Rose]]"). *[[1978]] &ndash; The last [[Volkswagen Beetle]] made in Germany leaves VW's plant in [[Emden]]. Beetle production in Latin America continues until 2003. *[[1981]] &ndash; [[Iran hostage crisis]]: United States and [[Iran]]ian officials sign an agreement to release 52 American hostages after 14 months of captivity. *[[1983]] &ndash; [[Nazi]] war criminal [[Klaus Barbie]] is arrested in [[Bolivia]]. * 1983 &ndash; The [[Apple Lisa]], the first commercial [[personal computer]] from [[Apple Inc.]] to have a [[graphical user interface]] and a [[computer mouse]], is announced. *[[1986]] &ndash; The first [[IBM PC]] [[computer virus]] is released into the wild. A boot sector virus dubbed [[Brain (computer virus)|(c)Brain]], it was created by the Farooq Alvi Brothers in [[Lahore]], [[Pakistan]], reportedly to deter unauthorized copying of the software they had written. *[[1991]] &ndash; [[Gulf War]]: [[Iraq]] fires a second [[Scud]] missile into [[Israel]], causing 15 injuries. *[[1993]] &ndash; [[Czech Republic]] and [[Slovakia]] join the [[United Nations]]. *[[1995]] &ndash; After being struck by lightning the crew of [[Bristow Flight 56C]] are forced to ditch. All 18 aboard are later rescued. *[[1996]] &ndash; The barge ''[[North Cape (ship)|North Cape]]'' oil spill occurs as an engine fire forces the tugboat ''Scandia'' ashore on Moonstone Beach in [[South Kingstown, Rhode Island]]. *[[1997]] &ndash; [[Yasser Arafat]] returns to [[Hebron]] after more than 30 years and joins celebrations over the handover of the last Israeli-controlled [[West Bank]] city. *[[1999]] &ndash; [[British Aerospace]] agrees to acquire the defence subsidiary of the [[General Electric Company plc]], forming [[BAE Systems]] in November 1999. *[[2007]] &ndash; Turkish-Armenian Journalist [[Hrant Dink]] is assassinated in front of his newspaper's Istanbul office by 17-year-old Turkish ultra-nationalist Ogün Samast. *[[2012]] &ndash; The Hong Kong-based file-sharing website [[Megaupload]] is shut down by the [[FBI]]. *[[2014]] &ndash; A [[2014 Bannu bombing|bomb attack]] on an army convoy in the city of [[Bannu]] kills at least 26 Pakistani soldiers and injures 38 others.
